# Network Troubleshooting Methodology

## Troubleshooting Steps

1. Verify network interface.

```bash
ip addr
```

2. Verify routing table.

```bash
ip route
```

3. Test gateway.

```bash
ping <gateway-ip>
```

4. Test Internet connectivity.

```bash
ping 8.8.8.8
```

5. Verify DNS.

```bash
nslookup google.com
```

6. Trace the network path.

```bash
tracepath google.com
```

## Best Practice

Follow a structured process rather than guessing. Record each observation before moving to the next step.
